The experimental circuit is designed using the PADS circuit
design software, which assists in selecting the PCB configura-
tion, stackup layout, internal layers and grounding. To pre-
vent unintended interference between different PCB layers, a
grounding layer is placed in the gap between any two layers.
Moreover, all PCB traces are designed to have a relatively
large width (0.5mm) to reduce the parasitic inductance, and
the spacings between electronic components are also made
sufficient large (1.0mm) to avoid spurious inductive coupling.
